---
/**
 * Station 6 - AI Assistance for Living in the Terminal
 * HAP's Learning Lab: Living in the Terminal
 *
 * Topics: Human architect role, informed approval, self-improving loop,
 *         harness engineering, AGENTS.md as correction mechanism
 * Characters: Grace Hopper (2 moments — overhearing in S3 and S5),
 *             Prof. Teeters (1 silent in S4 + closing thought in S8)
 * No Copilot interview this station — HAP references past interactions.
 *
 * STRUCTURE NOTE: 8 sections instead of the template's 12.
 * The 12-section template is designed for code-generation labs.
 * This station is about the human architect role — not prompt engineering
 * for code output. See reports/station6-redesign-proposal.md for rationale.
 */

import StationLayout from '../../layouts/StationLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';

const introContent = `
    <p><strong>Welcome to Station 6!</strong> I spent five stations learning the terminal. Navigation, files, deployment, context engineering, MCP servers. Along the way, a quiet question kept building: why does any of this matter if the agent can do it for me?</p>
    <p class="mt-1">The answer took a while to arrive. The agent knows what I tell it, reads what I give it, fixes what I point it at. But judgment about whether a fix is right, whether a rule belongs in AGENTS.md, whether a command is being run in the right place — that belongs to me. The agent has the tools. I have the full picture.</p>
    <p class="mt-1">Station 6 is not how to use AI. It is how to be the architect who uses it well. 🟠</p>
`;
---

<StationLayout
    stationNumber={6}
    title="AI Assistance for Living in the Terminal"
    subtitle="You are the architect. The agent is the tool. Know the difference."
    description="HAP learns to be the human architect — reading errors before pasting them, approving commands with understanding, and building a self-improving system with AGENTS.md."
    avatarImage="https://res.cloudinary.com/cynthia-teeters/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto,w_200,c_limit/v1/hap-laptop_xiewar.jpg"
    avatarAlt="HAP at a laptop, thinking carefully before approving a command"
    introContent={introContent}
    footerReminder="Read. Understand. Approve. Improve. That is the architect's loop."
    labName="Living in the Terminal"
>

